The paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep reinforcement learning policies, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper explores the limits of a model's vulnerability, which is a concept that is closely related to the study of neural network robustness (cs.NE).
